sub_title: Postdoctoral Researcher, natural products chemistry, Institute of Biology, Leiden University
summary: I am a natural products chemist (PhD and MSc), with background in pharmaceutical sciences (BSc). My prime research interest is the discovery of new drug leads from natural sources. For this, I am equipped with the following research tools: microbial isolation and culturing; LC-MS based metabolomics, dereplication, and molecular networking; chromatography; together with MS, MS/MS, UV, IR, and NMR based structure elucidation of small organic compounds.
